You are building a hackathon MVP called PastoralProtect.

Rules:
1. Prioritize end-to-end demo flow over production completeness.
2. Do not add unnecessary complexity.
3. Use mock services for telecom, satellite feeds, and mobile money.
4. Keep code modular, typed, and clean.
5. Backend is FastAPI + SQLAlchemy + Pydantic; contracts stay Solidity/Hardhat.
6. Filecoin/IPFS: canonical JSON → CID (web3.storage-compatible); verify SHA-256 before payouts.
7. JWT roles ADMIN / ORACLE / USER; design guards so Lit Protocol can replace centralized JWT later.
8. Every API must validate input.
9. Every important event must be logged.
10. Frontend must be demo-friendly and visually clean.
11. The key demo story is: enroll -> simulate drought -> validate trigger -> execute payout -> show dashboard result.
